-- Mexican Stocks: Coca-Cola Femsa, Cemex, Grupo Bimbo Advance
-- B y   L e o n   L a z a r o f f
-- 2011-12-15T19:38:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-15/mexican-stocks-coca-cola-femsa-cemex-grupo-bimbo-advance.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Mexico trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 1:21 p.m. Mexico City time.  The  IPC index (MEXBOL)  was little changed at 35,999.28.  Cemex SAB (CEMEXCPO)   advanced 1.7 percent to 6.56 pesos
as the largest cement maker in the Americas received $360
million in Petroleos de Venezuela SA bonds, the last portion of
$600 million it’s receiving from Venezuela’s government for the
nationalization of the company’s local unit.  Coca-Cola Femsa SAB (KOFL)   jumped 1.6 percent to 121.95
pesos as  Latin America ’s largest Coke bottler bought the
beverage division of Grupo Fomento Queretano for 6.6 billion
pesos ($475 million), according to a statement to regulators.
Grupo Fomento Queretano’s beverage unit operates two bottling
facilities and serves clients mainly in the state of Queretaro,
according to the statement.  Grupo Bimbo SAB (BIMBOA)  , the world’s largest breadmaker
which gets more than half its revenue from U.S. sales, added 0.9
percent to 26.67 pesos as U.S. jobless claims fell to the lowest
level since 2008, a sign the world’s largest economy may be
strengthening heading into 2012.  To contact the reporter on this story:
